article.headline: Mercer 99, Florida Gulf Coast 77
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. (AP) -- Guard James Florence scored a season-high 34 points as Mercer downed Florida Gulf Coast 99-77 on Thursday. Florence made seven 3-pointers, six in the second half when he scored 22. Guard Shaddean Aaron added 25 points, 20 in the second half. Forward Calvin Henry scored 14 and added 10 rebounds. Mercer scored 59 points in the second half to tie its season high in a 102-99 loss to VMI. The Bears (8-9, 3-1) hit 12-of-16 3-pointers in the second half and had a season high of 15 for the game. FGCU made nine 3-pointers in the second half. Forward Casey Wohlleb scored 25 for FGCU (5-12, 1-3) while guard Delvin Frankin added 15 points and guard Rob Quaintance 14.
